<Important Files>

aitetris - The AITetris executable.
resetdata.sh - A utility to reset (clear) all data and start from scratch.
board.dat - The actual tetris game and board state file.
*.cases - The temporary case files used to query the decision tree.
*.tree - The binary tree files generated by c5.0.
*.data - The data files used by the decision tree.

<How to Use it>

run ./resetdata.sh to reset all data files.

If you want to play tetris and let it learn from you, then run it in watch mode:

	aitetris board.dat w

If you want to play tetris and let the critic functions teach it:

	aitetris board.dat w

<Compiling>

To compile, simply type make in the src directory.
Extract out C50Demo_linux.tgz and ad the bin to your PATH.

